deck: Award-winning comics and concept artist from Serbia, born in 1979. He obtained his graphical design degree at the Faculty of Applied Arts in Belgrade.
name: Milos Slavkovic

deck: Leonid Pilipovic is Serbian artist known for his work on "L'Histoire secrète" ("The Secret History"), "Le Grand jeu" and "Ravermoon" series for French publishers, as well as for his alternative comics under pen name "Leo von Punkerstein".
name: Leonid Pilipovic

deck: Internationally awarded Serbian comic book artist and painter, notable for his work on Arthurian and Robert E. Howard themes, as well as his contribution to Serbian "Tarzan" series in 1980's.
name: Petar Meseldzija

description:
Eddie deAngelini is a long time comic book fan and collector. His love of comics began at a young age and continues to this day and his claim to fame is owning every issue of Amazing Spider-Man.

Eddie writes and draws Collectors, a weekly webcomic loosely based on Eddie's own life, marriage and comic collecting obsession. He currently lives in Los Angeles with his wife Kristen, where they plan together for the inevitable zombie apocalypse.
name: Eddie deAngelini

deck: Belgrade artist, writer and musician, known for his work on superhero comics, as well as his reboots of classical Serbian comics from Golden and Silver Age. He is also part of alternative comics scene and co-founder of Association of Serbian Comics Artists.
description:
Serbian comic-book and graphic novel creator, notable for his work on superhero comics, as well as for his reboots of classical Serbian comics from Golden and Silver Age: "Zigomar", "Maksim", "Tarcaneta", "Seleniti" etc.

He is known best for "Faktor 4" series written by Milan Konjević, "Munja" written by Zdravko Zupan and Zoran Stefanović, "Mobijeva kopilad" written by Bojan Milojević, as well as for "Vekovnici" written by Marko Stojanović.

Grbić is also co-founder of the Association of Serbian comics artists, curator of the regional exhibtions, workshops lecturer and active member of South-East European alternative comics scene.

As a musician, he was the bassist of the Belgrade rock bands "Viborg Dallas and "Vien lur" (formerly the "Delta 99"), now playing in "Dekoder".
name: Borivoje Grbic

deck: Awarded Belgrade artist, notable for his series for the top French publishers: "La Roue" ("The Wheel"), "La Meute de l'enfer", „Walkyrie“ etc.
name: Drazen Kovacevic

deck: Belgrade artist, painter and architect, notable for his cover illustrations for The Phantom, Modesty Blaise, James Bond, Batman, as well as for political comic strips for top Serbian dailies. He is member of "Bauhaus 7" art group since 1981.
name: Rade Tovladijac

deck: Internationally acclaimed Serbian painter and cartoonist, currently resident of Lucca, Italy. His work for French publishers ("Vincent et Van Gogh", "Le Cabaret des Muses") is being published in many languages all over Europe.
name: Gradimir Smudja

deck: Dobrosav "Bob" Zivkovic is one of the most popular illustrators and cartoonists of South-Eastern Europe, known as the master of all styles: realistic, stylized and caricatural.
name: Bob Zivkovic

deck: Masaaki Tezuka is the Japanese director of Godzilla vs. Megaguirus, Godzilla Against MechaGodzilla and Godzilla: Tokyo S.O.S..
name: Masaaki Tezuka

deck: Runs the Small Press and Alternative Comics Expo (SPACE) in Columbus OH and organizes and contributes to "Oh, Comics!".
description:
Bob Corby has been making comics for over 20 years. He put together the first Oh, Comics!, an annual anthology title, in 1988 through mail submissions and sold it at the Mid-Ohio Con here in Columbus. It has published over 100 comic creators, including David Mack, Matt Faezell, Scott Mills, Todd Webb, Teri S. Wood and Max Ink. It's generally around 100 pages.

He founded and runs Small Press & Alternative Comics Expo (SPACE) in Columbus OH since April 2000. It is an annual independent comic creators convention which has grown to more than a hundred artist exhibitors. He started the show as a gathering place for "the comics and the creators with no distractions." Every year it grants the SPACE prize.

He has drawn an illustrated many comics, including one shots like Test!, issue comics like Blue Bunny, mini-comics like Why I'm Not Musical Mini, and is working on a webcomic. He mostly works in black and white, but also enjoys color work.
name: Bob Corby
